     <div class="Features__FeaturesWrapper-u3gsp1-0 gMqJBj">
      <div class="Container-r2vo4x-0 Features__FeaturesContainer-u3gsp1-1 eYcWDh">
       <div class="Features__PrimaryText-u3gsp1-2 gFtHGj">
        <div class="SectionHeader__SectionHeaderContainer-sc-457x4u-0 htrakY" title="Features">
         <h1 class="Typography__H1-sc-1hs8ygb-0 SectionHeader__SectionHeaderTitle-sc-457x4u-1 bDRyEe" title="Features">
          Features
         </h1>
         <h2 class="Typography__H2-sc-1hs8ygb-1 SectionHeader__SectionHeaderTagline-sc-457x4u-2 SnQlA" title="Features">
          Why Video.js?
         </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
         Video.js is a web video player built from the ground up for an HTML5 world. It supports HTML5 video and modern streaming formats, as well as YouTube, Vimeo, and even Flash (through plugins, more on that later).
        </p>
        <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
         It supports video playback on desktop and mobile devices. The project was started mid 2010, and now has hundreds of contributors and is used on over 450,000 websites.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="Features__FeatureList-u3gsp1-3 DLgba">
        <div class="Features__Feature-u3gsp1-4 hcnqIe">
         <span>
          <img alt="abstract player illustration" src="/static/plays-everything-ba52dad7ecfe22cfd86e8fcc6cf1b835.svg"/>
          <h3 class="Typography__H3-sc-1hs8ygb-2 jAPvBu">
           Plays anything
          </h3>
          <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
           Plays traditional file formats such as MP4 and WebM, but also supports adaptive streaming formats such as HLS and DASH. Theres even a special UI for live streams!
          </p>
         </span>
        </div>
        <div class="Features__Feature-u3gsp1-4 hcnqIe">
         <span>
          <img alt="stylized abstract pencil" src="/static/easy-to-style-2768a245eb3a0b9cc76a7b98ad325c6c.svg"/>
          <h3 class="Typography__H3-sc-1hs8ygb-2 jAPvBu">
           Easy to style
          </h3>
          <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
           Video.js is designed to be a reliable and consistent base to build on top of. The player looks great out of the box, but can be easily styled with a little bit of extra CSS.
          </p>
         </span>
        </div>
        <div class="Features__Feature-u3gsp1-4 hcnqIe">
         <span>
          <img alt="abstract collection of checkboxes" src="/static/100s-of-plugins-cb406702b25103dfe67ecdd10bb7ae97.svg"/>
          <h3 class="Typography__H3-sc-1hs8ygb-2 jAPvBu">
           100s of plugins
          </h3>
          <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
           When you need to add additional functionality, a well-documented plugin architecture has your back. The community has already built hundreds of skins and plugins that you can install, such as Chromecast, IMA, even VR.
          </p>
         </span>
        </div>
        <div class="Features__Feature-u3gsp1-4 hcnqIe">
         <span>
          <img alt="abstract players of various sizes" src="/static/supported-everywhere-57ea05ed86118aba6f24e568480abef4.svg"/>
          <h3 class="Typography__H3-sc-1hs8ygb-2 jAPvBu">
           Supported everywhere
          </h3>
          <p class="Typography__P-sc-1hs8ygb-3 bWtpns">
           Your video should work everywhere your app does. The team makes an effort to support every modern browser we can, including desktop and mobile.
          </p>
         </span>
        </div>
       </div>
